Steps to install the DHCP Server.

Step 1 :
Installation of DHCP Server 
In Debian system using apt-get command
Command  : sudo apt-get -y install isc-dhcp-server
Step 2 :
Configuration of the DHCP Server
DHCP configuration file is present at /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf
Open the file with an editor and modify the DHCP File 
Command : $sudo nano /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf
Step 3:
Change Ip Address Of dhcpd.conf with your IP address.
Check the system's ip address using the following command:
Command : ifconfig
Change Save And Exit.
Step 4 :
Then to start the services use the command
Command : $sudo systemctl start isc-dhcp-server.service
And Now enable The Service.
Command :- $sudo systemctl enable isc-dhcp-server.service
